list-item.p: A host signal peptidase process the anchor junctions -C/prM, prM/E, E/NS1, and NS4A-“2K”/NS4B.
The viral NS3 serine protease needs NS2B as a cofactor, to process the C-anchor junctions of NS2A/NS2B, NS2B/NS3, NS3/NS4A, NS4A/"2K", and NS4B/NS5.
The furin of the host, or other furin binding proteins process the binding between pr/M.
The proteases of the host involved in separating the NS1/NS2A junction are unknown.
